00:51.292 --> 00:54.160
Since when do you hum songs?

00:54.162 --> 00:55.294
What are you talking
about?

00:55.296 --> 00:56.595
You were just humming.
Are you sure?

00:56.597 --> 00:59.565
Sometimes when my brain
really gets moving,

00:59.567 --> 01:02.134
it makes noise.

01:02.136 --> 01:04.437
How does your brain feel about
calculating the surface tension

01:04.438 --> 01:05.705
of the domain walls?

01:05.707 --> 01:08.007
Let's see.

01:09.210 --> 01:12.311
Hey! I <i> was</i> humming.

01:12.313 --> 01:15.514
One point
for Hufflepuff.

01:18.453 --> 01:20.386
What song is that?

01:20.388 --> 01:23.222
Well... Hum it again.

01:25.126 --> 01:26.926
Is that the <i> SpongeBob</i> song?

01:26.928 --> 01:31.097
♪ Who lives
in a pineapple ♪ Nope.

01:31.099 --> 01:32.498
Whatever. Can we just
get back to this?

01:32.500 --> 01:33.866
I feel like I know
what song that is,

01:33.868 --> 01:36.402
but I can't put
my finger on it.

01:36.404 --> 01:39.572
♪ My country, 'tis of thee ♪
No.

01:39.574 --> 01:42.241
It's just an earworm.
It'll come to you.

01:42.243 --> 01:45.044
Okay.

01:46.981 --> 01:48.948
♪ R-E-S-P-E-C-T ♪

01:48.950 --> 01:50.383
No.

01:50.385 --> 01:52.585
Is this what we're doing
the rest of the night?

01:52.587 --> 01:55.721
♪ I'm surprised
you have to ask... ♪

01:55.723 --> 01:59.191
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:59.193 --> 02:02.695
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:02.697 --> 02:04.330
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

02:04.332 --> 02:06.866
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:06.868 --> 02:09.535
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪<i> We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:09.537 --> 02:12.238
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:12.240 --> 02:14.106
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:14.108 --> 02:15.875
♪<i> Bang!</i> ♪

02:15.909 --> 02:19.909
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 9x10 ♪</font>
